   Matheson Urges Swift Action By Transportation Security Chief

   Washington, D.C.Rep. Jim Matheson, referencing the influx of world
   visitors to the Salt Lake City Airport for the Winter Olympic Games in
   two weeks, today urged the new Undersecretary for Transportation
   Security to speed security enhancement at U.S. airports.  Mathesona
   member of the House Transportation Committees Aviation
   Subcommitteespoke at todays Congressional hearing about the
   implementation of the Aviation and Transportation Security Act, and the
   effectiveness with which DOT and airlines have met the January 18
   baggage-screening deadline.  Mathesons legislation to test biometric
   technology to bolster security at airports is included in the Act.
   Click here for details.



