            Matheson Gains Funding for City After School Project

   Washington, D.C.Rep. Jim Matheson said today that $1.2 million for Salt
    Lake Citys YouthCity Empowerment Project is included in the Labor and
     Health and Human Services Appropriations measure that passed today.
   Matheson fought for funding for the project, which serves large numbers
   of young people left alone during after-school hours, with a particular
     focus on Salt Lake Citys growing ethnic population. Click here for
                                  details.

        Matheson Calls President's Education Bill Good News for Utah

    Washington D.C.Rep. Jim Matheson today called for a bipartisan effort
     in January to produce a targeted, temporary stimulus proposal that
   helps increase employment and investment, adequately assists displaced
      workers and doesnt drown the federal government in long-term red
                         ink.Click here for details.

                   Utah Downwinders Win Payments, Not IOUs

      Washington D.C.Rep. Jim Matheson said the passage of the Defense
    Authorization Bill is a victory for thousands of sick Utahns who were
    wrongly exposed to atomic fallout by the U.S. government decades ago
   but who havent received compensation since the trust fund paying claims
             ran out of money last year. Click here for details.

